      "body" : "@vogelito like I said you may have had couple of peers who were downloading blocks at the time, now they're done or you got different peers. It's not due to suddenly added disk, but simply a network (hence `bitcoin-msghand`) workload that pulls data from the disk. \r\nYou can google it to see what network traffic others get with full node, for any version. Because they get that much or more, that's why the docs about \"saving\" bandwidth were added.",
